    <question>
        <prompt>What was the immediate cause of the Spanish-American War?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">The Maine explosion</option>
            <option letter="b">Trade disputes</option>
            <option letter="c">Border conflicts</option>
            <option letter="d">Presidential assassination</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The explosion of the USS Maine in Havana harbor in 1898 provided the immediate catalyst for the Spanish-American War.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>What role did yellow journalism play in the war?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It opposed the war</option>
            <option letter="b">It promoted war fever</option>
            <option letter="c">It was neutral</option>
            <option letter="d">It supported Spain</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Yellow journalism, led by Hearst and Pulitzer, sensationalized Spanish actions and promoted war fever among the American public.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>The Teller Amendment declared that:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Cuba would become a U.S. state</option>
            <option letter="b">The U.S. would not annex Cuba</option>
            <option letter="c">Spain must pay war reparations</option>
            <option letter="d">The U.S. would occupy Cuba permanently</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Teller Amendment promised that the United States would not annex Cuba after defeating Spain.</explanation>
    </question>

